			<projectDesc><p>David Livingstone writes this portion of his diary entries over the recto and verso (NLS10703_002_037r and NLS10703_002_038v) of a single page of stationary marked "
					<hi rend="smallcaps">H.M. Consulate and Political Agency, Zanzibar</hi>" (NLS10703_002_038v). This stationary also bears the printed text "
					<hi rend="caps">On Her Majesty's Service.</hi>" This stationary was originally sent to Livingstone in an unmarked envelope (NLS10703_001_036r and NLS10703_001_039v) that Livingstone has also used to record diary entries. NLS10703_002_038v shows that these two folia were sent on 12/2/70 by John Kirk and were addressed to "Dr David Livingstone HRM Consul Ujiji &amp; Elsewhere". Livingstone has taken these two folia, folded each in half, and created an eight-page booklet. Livingstone's text is what is transcribed and represented in the Text Encoding Initiative (TEI) P5 XML encoding. Furthermore, the pages of the booklet have been numbered in the XML encoding according the Livingstone's scheme. Finally, the present folio includes the number "38" (in the upper right-hand corner) written in pencil in a second, unknown hand; and the address to Livingstone described above in a third, unknown hand (possibly John Kirk's).</p>
